<TEXT>
an 87yearold man hanged himself saturday in 
western japan after leaving a note saying he wanted to follow 
emperor hirohito in death police said 
a duty officer at national police headquarters said umanosuke ue 
used twine to hang himself in a shed near his home in wakayama 
about 280 miles southwest of tokyo 
the officer speaking on condition of anonymity said ues eldest 
son found the body and note about seven hours after the emperor died 
of intestinal cancer saturday 
the police officer said the note read in part i want to follow 
the emperor in death 
kyodo news service said ue once served in the japanese imperial 
army it said he had shown no signs of poor health but was proud of 
being born the same year as hirohito 
in ancient japan samurai warriors sometimes killed themselves to 
follow their lords in death in modern history gen maresuke nogi 
and his wife killed themselves on the day of emperor meijis funeral 
in 1912 
