<TEXT>
john donald robb a composer of 
symphonies expert on hispanic folk music and former dean of the 
university of new mexico college of fine arts died thursday he was 
96 
robb once a new york city lawyer with a corporate bond practice 
wrote nearly 100 surviving works they include symphonies and other 
orchestral works string quartets and other chamber music 
electronic music and musical stage pieces 
robb founded unms robb archive of southwestern folk music and 
made the first field recording for the archive he later published 
the authoritative book on new mexicos hispanic folk music 
in 1921 he married harriet block who survives him 
he moved to albuquerque in 1941 to head the universitys music 
department however he became acting dean of the fine arts school 
shortly after arriving and became permanent dean in 1947 
in 1960 he ran for congress on the republican party ticket 
losing to democrat thomas morris of tucumcari by 25000 votes 
born in 1892 in minneapolis robb entered yale in 1911 to study 
english literature he later studied law at the university of 
minnesota and harvard 
