<TEXT>
the federal government is spending more than 
800 million a year on irrigation subsidies for western farmers who 
grow crops already in surplus according to a congressional study 
administration officials acknowledge such subsidies exist but 
say they are a fourth a large as reported by a house subcommittee 
staff study and stem from agreements that are 20 or 30 years old 
the farmers in question are receiving water subsidies from the 
bureau of reclamation to help irrigate part of their land to grow 
surplus crops while receiving us department of agriculture money 
not to grow the same crops on other sections of their land said 
rep sam gejdenson dconn 
farmers must choose their subsidy said gejdenson who issued 
the report if they choose to continue to receive irrigation water 
at the subsidized rate they should not receive usda commodity 
benefits if they choose to receive usda commodity benefits they 
should have to pay the full unsubsidized cost of providing 
irrigation water to their farms 
gejdenson chairman of the house interior and insular affairs 
subcommittee on oversight and investigations is urging 
presidentelect bush to eliminate the double subsidies as a way 
to help reduce the budget deficit 
double subsidies increase the cost of the usda commodity 
programs place farmers who do not receive federal irrigation 
water at a disadvantage in the marketplace and make it more 
difficult for congress to approve administration requests for new 
and expanded water projects gejdenson wrote in a letter to bush 
but interior department officials who dismiss the subcommittees 
estimates as heavily inflated said the governments nointerest 
contracts with farmers for the irrigation programs would be 
difficult and costly to change 
most of our projects were built 20 to 30 years ago said 
mitch snow deputy assistant secretary for water and science we 
cannot go back in there and fiddle with the contracts unilaterally 
it would probably cost more to implement than it would result 
in savings he said we dont see that as beneficial 
