three members of a usbased dissident chinese 
group left shanghai on sunday after police accused them of breaking 
the law the official xinhua news agency said 
xinhua said the three a chineseamerican a chinesecanadian 
and a chinese student studying in the united states were heading 
for other countries but did not specify if they had left china yet 
american huang wencheng and canadian huang han were ordered to 
leave xinhua said it was not clear if tang guangzhong the chinese 
student and the only one of the three a chinese citizen also was 
ordered out and whether he would be allowed to return 
officials at the us and canadian embassies said chinese 
authorities had not told them about the expulsions the huangs do 
not appear to be related 
xinhua said the three acknowledged belonging to the new 
yorkbased chinese alliance for democracy a group set up by a 
former chinese citizen in 1983 that advocates a democratic 
revolution in china chinese officials have declared it an illegal 
reactionary organization and have banned its magazine china 
spring 
