the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in magnitude a reading of 75 means ground motion is 10 times 
stronger than one of 65 
an earthquake of magnitude 35 can cause slight damage 4 is 
capable of moderate damage 5 considerable damage 6 severe damage 
7 widespread damage and 8 tremendous damage 
